
Section

  Use Section to start a new document region. The blocks that follow are indented under that heading until the next section begins.
  
  Section is the document-level primitive that gives the rest of the output clear ownership.

  Owned blocks
    what: Paragraphs, records, lists, tables, and panels inherit the active section indent.
    why: That default makes CLI output read more like a document than a stream of unrelated prints.


Next section

  [INFO] Section boundaries reset ownership
    Starting another Section makes the boundary visible without requiring callers to manage indentation by hand.
